  Leaders have renewed calls for ODM leader Raila Odinga to back Wiper Party's Kalonzo Musyoka for presidency in 2022. The leaders said Kalonzo had supported leaders from other communities for presidency several times, and that it was time for others to support his candidacy. ALSO READ:

War on graft has turned skeptics into supporters Borabu MP Ben Momanyi described Kalonzo as a selfless leader who had twice sacrificed his presidential ambitions for Raila. “Kalonzo supported Raila in 2013, and 2017, and I don’t want to hear that Raila is running for the seat again,” said Momanyi. Kilome constituency MP Thadeus Nzambia said Kalonzo should not back down for Raila in 2022. The leaders spoke during a memorial ceremony for Nairobi Governor Mike Mbuvi's father Kioko Mbuvi at Mua Hills in Machakos County. Sonko also declared his support for Kalonzo’s presidential bid. Know if news is factual and true. Text 'NEWS' to 22840 and always receive verified news updates.